#: ../../S/space-cadet-keyboard.rst:28
msgid ""
"And of course each of these might also be typed with any combination of the "
"control, meta, hyper, and super keys. On this keyboard, you could type over "
"8000 different characters! This allowed the user to type very complicated "
"mathematical text, and also to have thousands of single-character commands "
"at his disposal. The keyboard of the Symbolics Lisp machine was a simplified"
" version, lacking Top and Front keys, that could only send about 2000 "
"characters."
msgstr ""
"そしてもちろん、これらの各々は、control、meta、hyper、superキーの任意の組み合わせとともにタイプすることもできた。このキーボードでは、8000を超える異なる文字をタイプできた!"
" これにより、ユーザーは非常に複雑な数学的テキストをタイプでき、また何千もの一文字コマンドを自由に使えた。Symbolics "
"Lispマシンのキーボードは、TopキーとFrontキーを欠く簡略版で、約2000文字しか送れなかった。"

#: ../../S/space-cadet-keyboard.rst:33
msgid ""
"Many hackers were actually willing to memorize the command meanings of that "
"many characters if it reduced typing time (this attitude obviously shaped "
"the interface of EMACS). Other hackers, however, thought having that many "
"bucky bits was overkill, and objected that such a keyboard can require three"
" or four hands to operate. See :ref:`bucky-bits`\\, :ref:`cokebottle`\\, "
":ref:`double-bucky`\\, :ref:`meta-bit`\\, :ref:`quadruple-bucky`\\."
msgstr ""
"多くのハッカーは、タイプ時間を減らせるなら、それほど多くの文字のコマンドの意味を実際に暗記する気があった(この態度は明らかにEMACSのインターフェースを形作った)。だが他のハッカーは、それほど多くのbucky"
" bitを持つのはやりすぎだと考え、そんなキーボードは操作に3本や4本の手が要りうると反論した。\\ :ref:`bucky-bits`\\ 、\\ "
":ref:`cokebottle`\\ 、\\ :ref:`double-bucky`\\ 、\\ :ref:`meta-bit`\\ 、\\ "
":ref:`quadruple-bucky`\\ を参照。"

